@Node GadInstall "Install Cache"
@{b}Installing a Cache@{ub}

This  gadget is used to install caches to selected devices.  To use it, you
must first select a device and unit in the list of cacheable devices.

Upon  pressing  Install,  a  new  window  with  a  bunch  of  gadgets  will
(hopefully) pop up, inactivating the main window.  This window is the Cache
configuration  window,  and  contains gadgetry to specify every detail of a
cache buffer:

           +---------------------------------------------------+
           @{"[X]" LINK GadICloseWindow} Cache Configuration For @{"[...]" LINK GadIWindowTitle}           [^][V] |
           +---------------------------------------------------+
           |    Organize As...                                 |
           |                              @{"Main Cache: [######]" LINK GadMainCache} |
           | @{"[###] Sets" LINK GadSets}                     @{"Overhead: [######]" LINK GadOverhead} |
           | @{"[###] Lines" LINK GadLines}                       @{"Total: [######]" LINK GadTotal} |
           | @{"[###] Prefetch" LINK GadPrefetch}           @{"Auto Configure: [S/M/L]" LINK GadAutoConfigure}  |
           +-------------------------+--------------------------+
           | @{"Mode:           [RW/RO]" LINK GadMode} |     @{"Type: [Memory/File]" LINK GadType} |
           | @{"Algorithm:    [LRU/RND]" LINK GadAlgorithm} | @{"Memory Type: [A/C/F/24]" LINK GadMemType} |
           | @{"Purge Timeout:    [###]" LINK GadPurgeTimeout} | @{"Filename: [________]" LINK GadFilename}@{"[?]" LINK GadGetFile} |
           | @{"Free After Purge:   [/]" LINK GadFreePurge} |                         |
           +-------------------------+-------------------------+
           | @{"Show Statistics Window: [                       ]" LINK GadShowStats} |
           +---------------------------------------------------+
           | @{" Okay " LINK GadIOkay}                                  @{" Cancel " LINK GadICancel} |
           +---------------------------------------------------+

For  a  more detailed explanation of individual controls, please select any
of the above links.


         @{i}- Real knowledge is to know the extent of ones ignorance@{ui}
